# bOS — Cursor Rules

You are working on bOS, a personal operating system with 17 AI agents and 47 skills.

## Architecture
- `AGENTS.md` — Cross-platform architecture overview
- `CLAUDE.md` — Full behavioral specification (Claude Code-specific)
- `.claude/agents/*.md` — 17 agent definitions (boss, ceo, coo, cto, cfo, cmo, sales, finance, coach, organizer, wellness, trainer, diet, mentor, teacher, reader, devlead)
- `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md` — 47 skills with YAML frontmatter
- `state/*.md` — User operational state (tasks, finances, habits, goals, etc.)
- `profile.md` — User identity and preferences
- `supabase/` — Pro mode database schemas

## Rules
- User data (`profile.md`, `state/*.md`) is sacred — never auto-modify
- System files are modifiable: agents, skills, CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md
- Skills use YAML frontmatter: name, description, user_invocable, command
- State files use Summary (first 25 lines) + Active + Archive structure
- Respond in the user's language (from profile.md)
- Every response ends with an actionable next step
- Check `state/SCHEMAS.md` for file format documentation

## Key Files When Editing
- Adding a skill → create `.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`, update `skills-registry.json`
- Adding an agent → create `.claude/agents/<name>.md`, update agent roster in `CLAUDE.md` and `AGENTS.md`
- Modifying state schema → update `state/SCHEMAS.md`
- Version bump → update `VERSION` + all references (see commit history for pattern)
